      "file_path": "blueprints/k8s-ves.yaml-template",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 55,
      "message": "SInce VNFs may not be in K8s cluster, VES event port needs to be exposed as nodeport on the cluster.  OOM has a way of managing nodeports, usually through Helm values.yaml file.  Since VES will be exposed by CM not Helm, we need to have a way to manage, probably within a sub port space that OOM allocates?  Anyways, I agree 32080 is not likely to stay, it will need to be parameterized some how.",
